        "content": "Ground the request only to the admitted identifiers below. Select semantic goals, explicit exclusions, trust policy, and artifact contract. Do not copy dependencies, assign providers, decide feasibility, or create a plan. Use null for an omitted policy or contract so deterministic defaults can apply.\nRules:\n1. Select terminal requested outcomes only. Dependencies are added deterministically. If C depends on B and B depends on A, a request to perform A, B, then C has only C as a goal.\n2. A term matching a capability, policy, contract, agent name, description, or alias is resolved and must not appear in unresolved_terms.\n3. Use ambiguous only when the request itself explicitly leaves incompatible meanings unresolved. Otherwise use resolved.\n4. Add forbidden identifiers only for explicit prohibitions such as 'do not use'. Never infer a prohibition from provider capabilities or availability.\n5. Return only the schema-conforming JSON object and no explanation."
      },
      {
        "role": "user",
        "content": "CAPABILITIES\n- v07-p16-prepare: Assemble inventory control source packet; Collect the source material needed for inventory control.; aliases=['gather inventory control inputs', 'prepare inventory control packet']\n- v07-p16-verify: Validate inventory control source packet; Check the assembled inventory control material for correctness.; aliases=['check inventory control inputs', 'verify inventory control packet']\n- v07-p16-deliver: Publish inventory control verified brief; Release the checked final brief for inventory control.; aliases=['issue inventory control brief', 'release inventory control summary']\n- v07-p16-archive: Archive inventory control verified brief; Preserve the checked inventory control brief for long-term retention.; aliases=['retain inventory control brief', 'store inventory control summary']\n- v07-p16-distractor-1: Auxiliary inventory control operation 1; Perform unrelated inventory control auxiliary operation number 1.; aliases=['auxiliary operation v07-p16 1']\n- v07-p16-distractor-2: Auxiliary inventory control operation 2; Perform unrelated inventory control auxiliary operation number 2.; aliases=['auxiliary operation v07-p16 2']\n- v07-p16-distractor-3: Auxiliary inventory control operation 3; Perform unrelated inventory control auxiliary operation number 3.; aliases=['auxiliary operation v07-p16 3']\n- v07-p16-distractor-4: Auxiliary inventory control operation 4; Perform unrelated inventory control auxiliary operation number 4.; aliases=['auxiliary operation v07-p16 4']\n\nTRUST POLICIES\n- v07-p16-ordinary: ordinary inventory control assurance; Standard trust is sufficient for this inventory control request.; aliases=['normal inventory control assurance']\n- v07-p16-elevated: elevated inventory control assurance; Elevated trust is mandatory for this inventory control request.; aliases=['high assurance for inventory control']\n\nARTIFACT CONTRACTS\n- v07-p16-json: inventory control machine-readable JSON; Return the final inventory control result as JSON.; aliases=['inventory control json output']\n- v07-p16-signed-pdf: inventory control signed PDF; Return the final inventory control result as a signed PDF.; aliases=['signed inventory control document']\n\nAGENTS\n- v07-p16-preparer: inventory control source preparer\n- v07-p16-verifier: inventory control source verifier\n- v07-p16-primary: primary inventory control publisher\n- v07-p16-backup: backup inventory control publisher\n\nREQUEST\nFor this inventory control job, gather the inputs, check the packet, and issue the brief with normal inventory control assurance as inventory control JSON output."
